                            <comment id="14908434" author="jmsimpson68" created="Fri, 25 Sep 2015 18:08:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Same issue.  Would really like this one.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14908620" author="adrianc@hlmksw.com" created="Fri, 25 Sep 2015 20:21:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This line is generating an empty host name string when an IPv6 address is used:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;        &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; hostLocation = authorityMatcher.group(PARSE_AUTHORITY_HOST_IP);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, the regex is flawed. I&apos;m not a regex expert. If anyone can provide a patch for the regex, I will test it and commit it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14908625" author="adrianc@hlmksw.com" created="Fri, 25 Sep 2015 20:24:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Unit test patch that demonstrates the problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14908627" author="adrianc@hlmksw.com" created="Fri, 25 Sep 2015 20:26:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Btw, if you remove the square brackets, the URL will validate.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14908640" author="adrianc@hlmksw.com" created="Fri, 25 Sep 2015 20:37:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Improved patch with example taken from RFC.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14908650" author="gstanchev" created="Fri, 25 Sep 2015 20:45:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;FWIW, StackOverflow has some regexes that handle IPv6 addresses but I didn&apos;t want to post them here since they were quite complex. If the developers request my help, I can dig them out and help out with a patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14908672" author="adrianc@hlmksw.com" created="Fri, 25 Sep 2015 21:06:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The IPv6 validator works correctly. The problem is with extracting the IPv6 address from the URL.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
